      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>His robes are torn and stained with vomit. He turns his eyeless face toward you, wiping his mouth. "Come for a story?" His speech is slurred and his voice ragged. "I told all the best stories." 

He slaps his chest. "It's my club, anyway."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What club?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You need help."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm going to go now..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Wait!" He grabs your collar and pulls you close. "You have to be a member." His breath reeks of stale vomit. "Show them this." He shoves a ring into your hand.

He staggers to the side and addresses no one in particular "And tell them that no one throws me out of the Club for Prefined and Restigious Gentlemen..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Club for Refined and Prestigious Gentlemen!" He prods your shoulder. "Wait. If you don't know about the Club, you must be-"

He heaves, catching at his chest. After several precarious seconds, he recovers.

"Where was I? Oh, you must be here about the ring. The ring." He shoves it into your hand.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Have to have that to get into the lounge." He hiccups. "They don't let just anyone in, you know." He wipes a hand on his shredded robe. "It's the most exclusive club in Defiance Bay."

He slaps you on the back. "And whatever you do, don't tell them you're new, or-" he turns away, overcome by a fit of dry heaving.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do not!" He shakes a finger in your face. "I am the most experienced member of the Club for Refined and Prestigious Gentlemen." He prods your shoulder. "I never need help.

"I just need..." He falls silent for several seconds. "The ring!" He shoves a ring into your hand.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can't kick me out like that! Been around longer'n any of them..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The new members are all phonies! Got no class."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hard enough to find a place with sophisticated company."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
